The paper deals with the problem of computing sample points in real algebraic sets defined by rank defects in linear matrices, which has applications in control theory, computational geometry, optimization, etc. The matrices in question have a Hankel structure, which is a symmetric structure that appears in many areas of engineering sciences. Therefore, cs.SY (systems and control), cs.NA (numerical analysis), cs.DS (discrete mathematics), cs.CG (computational geometry), and cs.LG (machine learning) are all possible sub-categories that this paper could belong to. However, since the paper focuses on the special structure of Hankel matrices and its implications for solving semi-definite programming problems, cs.SY is the most likely sub-category.
